# Backend credentials for the legacy SMB1 share(s).
#
# Copy this file to lab/backend-creds.env (untracked — gitignored by
# the *creds* glob in .gitignore) and fill in the real password(s).
# The original credential is documented in
# docs/sketch-smb1-smb3-proxy.sh for reference.
#
# lab/run-scenario.sh sources lab/backend-creds.env automatically (or
# whatever path you pass with --backend-creds FILE) before invoking the
# scenario, so the variables below land in the scenario's environment.

# --- Single-share scenarios (backend-mount, frontend-share, end-to-end) ---
#
# Only SC_BACKEND_PASS is required; the other SC_* values default
# inside the scenarios to the production legacy SMB1 backend coordinates.

SC_BACKEND_PASS='replace-me-with-the-real-engineering_user-password'

# Optional overrides (uncomment if your backend differs from defaults):
# SC_SHARE_NAME='Engineering$'
# SC_BACKEND_IP='172.29.137.1'
# SC_BACKEND_USER='engineering_user'
# SC_BACKEND_DOMAIN='LEGACY'
# SC_BACKEND_MOUNT='/mnt/legacy/Engineering_'
# SC_FORCE_USER='engineering_user'

# --- Multi-share scenario (multi-share) ---
#
# Multi-share configures two shares from the SAME backend with
# DIFFERENT users + DIFFERENT passwords + DIFFERENT AD groups, which
# is the actual operational use case the multi-share refactor was
# built for.
#
# SC_BACKEND_PASS_A defaults to SC_BACKEND_PASS above; SC_BACKEND_PASS_B
# must be supplied explicitly. Set the user/group/force-user vars too
# if your second backend account isn't the placeholder defaults.

# SC_BACKEND_PASS_A='same-as-SC_BACKEND_PASS-or-different'
# SC_BACKEND_PASS_B='replace-me-with-the-real-second-account-password'
# SC_SHARE_A='Engineering$'
# SC_SHARE_B='Drawings$'
# SC_BACKEND_USER_A='engineering_user'
# SC_BACKEND_USER_B='drawuser'
# SC_GROUP_A='LAB\Domain Users'
# SC_GROUP_B='LAB\Domain Admins'
# SC_FORCE_USER_A='engineering_user'
# SC_FORCE_USER_B='drawuser'
